    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability mass function (PMF) for the Hypergeometric distribution is"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "P(x) = \\frac{\\binom{g}{x}\\binom{b}{n-x}}{\\binom{g+b}{n}},"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "where "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "0 \\le x \\le n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "n-b \\le x \\le g"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "for P(x) the probability of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "x"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " good results in the drawn sample,\ng = "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ngood"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", b = "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "nbad"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", and n = "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "nsample"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Consider an urn with black and white marbles in it, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "ngood"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " of them\nare black and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "nbad"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " are white. If you draw "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "nsample"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " balls without\nreplacement, then the hypergeometric distribution describes the\ndistribution of black balls in the drawn sample."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Note that this distribution is very similar to the binomial\ndistribution, except that in this case, samples are drawn without\nreplacement, whereas in the Binomial case samples are drawn with\nreplacement (or the sample space is infinite). As the sample space\nbecomes large, this distribution approaches the binomial."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nLentner, Marvin, \"Elementary Applied Statistics\", Bogden\nand Quigley, 1972.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Hypergeometric Distribution.\" From\nMathWorld--A Wolfram Web Resource.\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/HypergeometricDistribution.html",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "3\n\nWikipedia, \"Hypergeometric distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypergeometric_distribution",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "ngood, nbad, nsamp = 100, 2, 10"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "# number of good, number of bad, and number of samples"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = we.random.hypergeometric(ngood, nbad, nsamp, 1000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "from matplotlib.pyplot import hist"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "hist(s)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "#   note that it is very unlikely to grab both bad items"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Suppose you have an urn with 15 white and 15 black marbles.\nIf you pull 15 marbles at random, how likely is it that\n12 or more of them are one color?"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = we.random.hypergeometric(15, 15, 15, 100000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "sum(s>=12)/100000. + sum(s<=3)/100000."
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "#   answer = 0.003 ... pretty unlikely!"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
